                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 3691/70.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of Nicaragua</gloss> to
                        President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-02-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 16, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Being informed of your second cablegram offering your valuable aid to bring about
                    a practical solution of the Nicaragua-Honduras conflict in conformity with the
                    view that reparation for offenses should be exacted, I thank you for this proof
                    of friendship, and I pray that Honduras may not show reluctance to the
                    philanthropic offices of Your Excellency, for I fear that the continuances of
                    the forces face to face may precipitate a rupture.</p>
                <p>I reiterate to you my high consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. S. Zelaya.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
